Relation between GDP and suicide mortality
The goal of this workflow is to analyze if there is any impact of key
economic indicators such as GDP per capita and unemployment rates on
The WHO data on the number of suicides in various countries for different
years was imported onto this workflow from a .sql file.
Data on GDP, population and unemployment was extracted and enriched
with the existing data from the WorldBank API.
After successfully loading the data from these sources, ETL tasks are
performed within this knime workflow and we end up with correlations
between suicide mortality and GDP per capita as well as unemployment
We also run a linear regression model, the scatter plot helps
visualizing the relationship between GDP per capita or unemployment
